		<title>03MY DAD'S JOB</title>
		<content>   My dad is a miner at Kilnhurst pit. 
 He does different jobs every day.  My 
 brother is also training to be a      
 miner.  My dad works on the coal      
 face.  Underground there is a machine 
 called a sheerer.  It cuts the coal   
 out.  It then goes onto a chain and   
 onto a conveyor belt which loads into 
 mine cars.  The coal then travels     
 underground to Manvers pit where it   
 is brought out to the surface, washed 
 and sent to power stations.  My dad   
 has worked at Kilnhurst pit for twenty
 six years.                            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
